----

- causal link between experience and belief
- only beliefs can stand in normative relations to other beliefs

- From Putnam's paper in Reading ..McDowell: "if our beliefs lack rational connections to experiences - if experiences are _only_ causes of those beliefs, and not also _justifiers_ - then it is impossible to see how our beliefs have _empirical content_ at all."

